item.description:
arXiv:2504.15907v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: The existence of the meromorphic solutions to Fermat type delay-differential equation
  \begin{equation}
  f^n(z)+a(f^{(l)}(z+c))^m=p_1(z)e^{a_1z^k}+p_2(z)e^{a_2z^k}, \nonumber
  \end{equation}
  is derived by using Nevanlinna theory under certain conditions, where $k\ge1$, $m,$ $n$ and $l\ge0$ are integers, $p_i$ are nonzero entire functions of order less than $k$, $c$, $a$ and $a_i$ are constants, $i=1,2$. These results not only improve the previous results from Zhu et al. [J. Contemp. Math. Anal. 59(2024), 209-219], Qi et al. [Mediterr. J. Math. 21(2024), article no. 122], but also completely solve two conjectures posed by Gao et al. [Mediterr. J. Math. 20(2023), article no. 167].Some examples are given to illustrate our results.
